{"orig":"/Users/kalaverin/src/lang/nim/lib/pure/collections/heapqueue.nim","nimble":"stdlib","moduleDescription":"The <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">heapqueue</span></span></tt> module implements a <a class=\"reference external\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Binary_heap\">binary heap data structure</a> that can be used as a <a class=\"reference external\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Priority_queue\">priority queue</a>. They are represented as arrays for which <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">a</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"Identifier\">k</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">]</span> <span class=\"Operator\">&lt;=</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">a</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"DecNumber\">2</span><span class=\"Operator\">*</span><span class=\"Identifier\">k</span><span class=\"Operator\">+</span><span class=\"DecNumber\">1</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">]</span></span></tt> and <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">a</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"Identifier\">k</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">]</span> <span class=\"Operator\">&lt;=</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">a</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"DecNumber\">2</span><span class=\"Operator\">*</span><span class=\"Identifier\">k</span><span class=\"Operator\">+</span><span class=\"DecNumber\">2</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">]</span></span></tt> for all indices <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">k</span></span></tt> (counting elements from 0). The interesting property of a heap is that <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">a</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"DecNumber\">0</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">]</span></span></tt> is always its smallest element.\n<h1><a class=\"toc-backref\" id=\"basic-usage\" href=\"#basic-usage\">Basic usage</a></h1>\n<h1><a class=\"toc-backref\" id=\"usage-with-custom-objects\" href=\"#usage-with-custom-objects\">Usage with custom objects</a></h1><p>To use a <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">HeapQueue</span></span></tt> with a custom object, the <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Operator\">&lt;</span></span></tt> operator must be implemented.</p>\n","entries":[{"name":"HeapQueue","type":"skType","line":53,"col":19,"code":"HeapQueue[T] = object","description":"A heap queue, commonly known as a priority queue."},{"name":"initHeapQueue","type":"skProc","line":57,"col":0,"code":"proc initHeapQueue[T](): HeapQueue[T]","signature":{"return":"HeapQueue[T]","genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"<p>Creates a new empty heap.</p>\n<p>Heaps are initialized by default, so it is not necessary to call this function explicitly.</p>\n<p><strong>See also:</strong></p>\n<ul class=\"simple\"><li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#toHeapQueue,openArray[T]\">toHeapQueue proc</a></li>\n</ul>\n"},{"name":"len","type":"skProc","line":67,"col":0,"code":"proc len[T](heap: HeapQueue[T]): int {.inline.}","signature":{"return":"int","arguments":[{"name":"heap","type":"HeapQueue[T]"}],"pragmas":["inline"],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"Returns the number of elements of <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">heap</span></span></tt>."},{"name":"`[]`","type":"skProc","line":75,"col":0,"code":"proc `[]`[T](heap: HeapQueue[T]; i: Natural): lent T {.inline.}","signature":{"return":"lent T","arguments":[{"name":"heap","type":"HeapQueue[T]"},{"name":"i","type":"Natural"}],"pragmas":["inline"],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"Accesses the i-th element of <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">heap</span></span></tt>."},{"name":"items","type":"skIterator","line":79,"col":0,"code":"iterator items[T](heap: HeapQueue[T]): lent T {.inline.}","signature":{"return":"lent T","arguments":[{"name":"heap","type":"HeapQueue[T]"}],"pragmas":["inline"],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"Iterates over each item of <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">heap</span></span></tt>."},{"name":"push","type":"skProc","line":144,"col":0,"code":"proc push[T](heap: var HeapQueue[T]; item: sink T)","signature":{"arguments":[{"name":"heap","type":"var HeapQueue[T]"},{"name":"item","type":"sink T"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"Pushes <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">item</span></span></tt> onto <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">heap</span></span></tt>, maintaining the heap invariant."},{"name":"toHeapQueue","type":"skProc","line":149,"col":0,"code":"proc toHeapQueue[T](x: openArray[T]): HeapQueue[T]","signature":{"return":"HeapQueue[T]","arguments":[{"name":"x","type":"openArray[T]"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"<p>Creates a new HeapQueue that contains the elements of <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span></span></tt>.</p>\n<p><strong>See also:</strong></p>\n<ul class=\"simple\"><li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#initHeapQueue\">initHeapQueue proc</a></li>\n</ul>\n"},{"name":"pop","type":"skProc","line":164,"col":0,"code":"proc pop[T](heap: var HeapQueue[T]): T","signature":{"return":"T","arguments":[{"name":"heap","type":"var HeapQueue[T]"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"Pops and returns the smallest item from <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">heap</span></span></tt>, maintaining the heap invariant."},{"name":"find","type":"skProc","line":179,"col":0,"code":"proc find[T](heap: HeapQueue[T]; x: T): int","signature":{"return":"int","arguments":[{"name":"heap","type":"HeapQueue[T]"},{"name":"x","type":"T"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"Linear scan to find the index of the item <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span></span></tt> or -1 if not found."},{"name":"contains","type":"skProc","line":191,"col":0,"code":"proc contains[T](heap: HeapQueue[T]; x: T): bool","signature":{"return":"bool","arguments":[{"name":"heap","type":"HeapQueue[T]"},{"name":"x","type":"T"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"Returns true if <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span></span></tt> is in <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">heap</span></span></tt> or false if not found. This is a shortcut for <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">find</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Identifier\">heap</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">x</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"Operator\">&gt;=</span> <span class=\"DecNumber\">0</span></span></tt>."},{"name":"del","type":"skProc","line":196,"col":0,"code":"proc del[T](heap: var HeapQueue[T]; index: Natural)","signature":{"arguments":[{"name":"heap","type":"var HeapQueue[T]"},{"name":"index","type":"Natural"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"Removes the element at <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">index</span></span></tt> from <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">heap</span></span></tt>, maintaining the heap invariant."},{"name":"replace","type":"skProc","line":210,"col":0,"code":"proc replace[T](heap: var HeapQueue[T]; item: sink T): T","signature":{"return":"T","arguments":[{"name":"heap","type":"var HeapQueue[T]"},{"name":"item","type":"sink T"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"<p>Pops and returns the current smallest value, and add the new item. This is more efficient than <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">pop</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span></span></tt> followed by <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">push</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span></span></tt>, and can be more appropriate when using a fixed-size heap. Note that the value returned may be larger than <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">item</span></span></tt>! That constrains reasonable uses of this routine unless written as part of a conditional replacement.</p>\n<p><strong>See also:</strong></p>\n<ul class=\"simple\"><li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#pushpop,HeapQueue[T],sinkT\">pushpop proc</a></li>\n</ul>\n"},{"name":"pushpop","type":"skProc","line":230,"col":0,"code":"proc pushpop[T](heap: var HeapQueue[T]; item: sink T): T","signature":{"return":"T","arguments":[{"name":"heap","type":"var HeapQueue[T]"},{"name":"item","type":"sink T"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"<p>Fast version of a <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">push</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span></span></tt> followed by a <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">pop</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span></span></tt>.</p>\n<p><strong>See also:</strong></p>\n<ul class=\"simple\"><li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#replace,HeapQueue[T],sinkT\">replace proc</a></li>\n</ul>\n"},{"name":"clear","type":"skProc","line":247,"col":0,"code":"proc clear[T](heap: var HeapQueue[T])","signature":{"arguments":[{"name":"heap","type":"var HeapQueue[T]"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"Removes all elements from <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">heap</span></span></tt>, making it empty."},{"name":"`$`","type":"skProc","line":256,"col":0,"code":"proc `$`[T](heap: HeapQueue[T]): string","signature":{"return":"string","arguments":[{"name":"heap","type":"HeapQueue[T]"}],"genericParams":[{"name":"T"}]},"description":"Turns a heap into its string representation."}]}